PART 1 — STRING FUNCTIONS

Used to manipulate text data (names, titles, emails).

1. LPAD & RPAD (Padding)
- LPAD(title, 20, '*')
- RPAD(title, 20, '*')

Meaning
- Adds characters to make a string a fixed length.

Logic
- Used for formatting outputs in reports.

2. SUBSTRING
- SUBSTRING(title, 1, 9)
Extracts part of text.
Syntax Logic:
- SUBSTRING(column, start_position, length)

3. CONCAT
-CONCAT(first_name, '.', last_name)
Joins multiple strings.

4. REVERSE
- REVERSE(title)
Flips text backwards.

5. LENGTH
- LENGTH(title)
Counts number of characters.
Used for filtering based on size.

6. Extracting Email Domain
- SUBSTRING(email, LOCATE('@', email) + 1)
Logic Steps
Find @
Extract everything after it

7. SUBSTRING_INDEX
- SUBSTRING_INDEX(email,'@',1)
Gets part before @

8. UPPER / LOWER
- Convert text case.
- Used for case-insensitive searches.

9. LEFT & RIGHT
- LEFT(title,2)
- RIGHT(title,3)
Extract characters from start/end.

10. CASE (Conditional Logic)
- CASE WHEN condition THEN result END
Works like IF-ELSE.

11. REPLACE
- REPLACE(title,'A','x')
Replaces characters.

12. REGEXP (Pattern Matching)
Pattern -	Meaning
[aeiou]$ -	Ends with vowel
{3} -	Exactly 3 repetitions
- Used for advanced filtering.

## PART 2 — MATH FUNCTIONS
- Used for calculations.

Important: ^ in MySQL
- rental_rate ^ 3
^ is bitwise XOR, not power.

Use:
- POWER(rental_rate,3)

Aggregates
- SUM(amount)
  COUNT(payment_id)
  AVG = SUM/COUNT
Used with GROUP BY.

RAND
- Generates random numbers.

MOD
- Remainder after division.

CEIL / FLOOR
- Round up / round down.

ROUND
- Controls decimal precision.

## PART 3 — DATE FUNCTIONS
- Used for time-based analysis.

DATEDIFF
- DATEDIFF(return_date, rental_date)
Finds number of days between dates.

Extract Date Parts
Function -	Purpose
YEAR() -	Extract year
DAYNAME() -	Day of week
MONTHNAME() -	Month name

NOW vs CURDATE
Function -	Output
NOW()	- Date + Time
CURDATE() -	Date only

INTERVAL
- NOW() - INTERVAL 1 DAY
Used for recent data filtering.

PART 4 — TYPE CASTING
CAST:
- CAST(amount AS CHAR)
- CAST('2017-08-25' AS DATETIME)
Converts data types.

MySQL Auto Conversion
- amount_str + 10
MySQL tries to convert text to number automatically.
